  "body": "**bug**\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nControlled Input type=\"date\" doesn't trigger onChange by pressing the clear button on iOS Datepicker Keyboard. This only happens on controlled input, uncontrolled works fine.\r\n \r\nReproduced on **iPhone 6 iOS 11.2.2 Safari**.\r\n\r\nDemo React 16.2: [jsfiddle](https://jsfiddle.net/z0jhLq8y/1/)\r\nDemo React 15.6.2 [jsfiddle](https://jsfiddle.net/23ye3qzz/2/)\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nControlled Input date should trigger onChange by pressing the clear button.\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n- react: 16.2 & 15.6.2\r\n- react-dom: 16.2 & 15.6.2\r\n- OS: iOS 11.2.2\r\n- Browser: Safari\r\n- Device: iPhone 6, iPhone SE\r\n",
